":"Coding"},{"name":"Creative"},{"name":"General Coding"},{"name":"Ramblings"}],"tags":[{"name":"Coding"},{"name":"Design"},{"name":"Inspiration"},{"name":"JS"},{"name":"Storytelling"},{"name":"Type"},{"name":"Yellow"}]}},{"node":{"id":"33a09e38-75d8-5d09-b045-a1b22a1e0356","slug":"creative-and-development-inspiration-5-feature-highlights","template":"","format":"standard","title":"Creative and Development Inspiration 5: Feature Highlights","date":"2017-11-20, 13:19:07","modified":"2017-11-20, 13:22:04","excerpt":"<p>Finding ways to display hidden information for users can be tough. The number of times brochure websites have required some level of user engagement and I have had to scour the web for examples such as these. I thought I should share. &nbsp; Project Feature Highlights By adding tooltips into div elements they can be positioned anywhere [&hellip;]</p>\n","featured_media":{"localFile":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1.9569471624266144,"src":"/static/6d098269bafc3ddbfa350ee8cd3d22ff/3c1c5/hover-tooltip.jpg","srcSet":"/static/6d098269bafc3ddbfa350ee8cd3d22ff/a9e03/hover-tooltip.jpg 250w,\n/static/6d098269bafc3ddbfa350ee8cd3d22ff/1605e/hover-tooltip.jpg 500w,\n/static/6d098269bafc3ddbfa350ee8cd3d22ff/3c1c5/hover-tooltip.jpg 1000w","sizes":"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px"}}},"title":"Hover Tooltip Header","alt_text":"Animated button tooltips"},"categories":[{"name":"Coding"},{"name":"Creative"},{"name":"General Coding"}],"tags":[{"name":"Animated"},{"name":"Coding"},{"name":"CSS"},{"name":"Design"},{"name":"Features"},{"name":"Highlights"},{"name":"Hover"},{"name":"JS"},{"name":"Mouseover"},{"name":"Snippets"},{"name":"Teaching"},{"name":"Tooltips"}]}},{"node":{"id":"c80c112a-50b5-52bc-9ba6-380b4c3a32eb","slug":"creative-and-development-inspiration-4-hidden-menus","template":"","format":"standard","title":"Creative and Development Inspiration 4: Hidden Menus","date":"2017-11-13, 10:05:25","modified":"2017-11-13, 13:48:40","excerpt":"<p>Today&#8217;s post is focusing on code snippets for hidden menus. These could be used on both mobile and large devices. Although they are not particularly attractive menus, I am focusing more on the usability and style. The purpose is to help inspire. &nbsp; Simple multilevel menu This menu is a code snippet from Cody House. [&hellip;]</p>\n","featured_media":{"localFile":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1.829268292682927,"src":"/static/5eccdd0964125c62a43ad3f876db702c/db7af/Google-Material-Mobile-Menus.jpg","srcSet":"/static/5eccdd0964125c62a43ad3f876db702c/8f9a6/Google-Material-Mobile-Menus.jpg 250w,\n/static/5eccdd0964125c62a43ad3f876db702c/6a7a1/Google-Material-Mobile-Menus.jpg 500w,\n/static/5eccdd0964125c62a43ad3f876db702c/db7af/Google-Material-Mobile-Menus.jpg 750w","sizes":"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px"}}},"title":"Google Material Mobile Menus","alt_text":"Google Material Mobile Menus"},"categories":[{"name":"Coding"},{"name":"Creative"},{"name":"General Coding"}],"tags":[{"name":"Coding"},{"name":"CSS"},{"name":"Design"},{"name":"Google"},{"name":"Hover"},{"name":"JS"},{"name":"Material"},{"name":"Menu"},{"name":"Mouseover"}]}}],"pathPrefix":"tag","first":false,"last":true,"index":7,"pageCount":7,"additionalContext":{"tagName":"JS"}}}